  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You cause a cocoon to rapidly form around one creature you touch. If the target is unwilling, you must make a <strong>melee spell attack</strong> to target them. On a miss, the spell fails. While inside the cocoon, the target is restrained, and gains full cover against all effects that would target it.</p><p>The cocoon has an AC of 16, 200 hit points, automatically fails Dexterity and <strong>Strength saving throw</strong>s, has vulnerability to fire damage, and is immune to effects that would force it to make any other kind of save.</p><p>When the spell ends, the cocoon dissolves and the creature inside regains 50 hit points. As an action, you can end the spell early.</p>",
